			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				This bill was written to defend credit card companies from bankruptcy. They already insert something called "universal default" into the weasel words on the so called "agreement" which let them jack up your rates with them if you are late with any other payer.
<br />

<br />
Sample of "universal default"
<br />
You have a credit card with a_bank149238409238.
<br />
You have a water bill.
<br />
You forget to pay water bill one month.
<br />
a_bank149238409238 excercises their universal default claws and jacks up your credit card rate.
<br />

<br />
Poppa, credit card rates run as high as 42% apr in the US.
<br />

<br />
Chapter 7 means that you sell off your assets, and divide the proceeds among the folks you owe money to.
<br />
Chapter 13 means that you have to pay off every debt, and can't get out of any of them.
<br />

<br />
The bill basically stated that 35k-210k people who would have filed chapter 7 will be compelled to go into chapter 13.
<br />

<br />
Americans live within 1 month of bankruptcy. For most people, losing their job or getting in an accident bad enough to involve a trip to the hospital and they will quickly lose their house, car and other worldly possessions.
<br />

<br />
This bill guarantees that credit card companies don't have to be responsible for their mistakes: you are. Forever and ever.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
