				<div class="postbody">
				You know what I've started getting in the mail recently are "checks" that are really loans.
<br />

<br />
Last week I got a check for 5,200 dollars from some bank.  Reading the fine print, it was an actual check.  I could take it to a bank and deposit it, or @#%$.  by doing so, I agreed to a loan at something like 31% APR.  I forget the details, but with the rolling interest putting that 5,200 dollars in the bank would have cost me 9,600 dollars to pay back.
<br />

<br />
But, if someone were desperate for money, this would be great...except for the fact that they'd just be fucking themselves, dropping further into debt.  Lot of uneducated people wont understand this either.  They see a check, ready to roll, for 5,200 dollars.  
<br />

<br />
Thats @#%$.<br />
