				<div class="postbody">
				This is PRECISELY the method people were sold into indentured servitude in pre-industrial England and PRECISELY why we have bankrupcy laws.
<br />

<br />
The poor and desperate were given loans simply to get by.  The economy literally adjusted to requiring debt to live and people found themselves put into bondage.  Pretty soon, even people not in debt but destitute were added to these private work farms.  This is very bad juju.
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
What is the remedy for people that do not pay their debts?  Is there one?   If this bill does not provide it, the remedy is in the wings waiting and the only remedy government can enforce is force.<br />
