			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Heard a bit on this on the radio the other day. 
<br />

<br />
Basicly if you file chap. 7, theres no more walking away from your debts.
<br />

<br />
If your income is more than Your states median income your forced to pay a portion of the debt back... Regardless of the fact you've filed for bankruptcy. It simply makes discharging the debts harder for creditors. I doubt I've heard this exactly correct... Talk to a lawyer or 2.
<br />

<br />
Judges are supposed to take extreme cases and hard luck cases in to consideration, but we've all heard that one before.
<br />

<br />
Additionally some individuals due to income may be forced into chap. 13.
<br />

<br />
This means you dont get a choice, you get time... no portion of your debt is removed and you have 5 years to pay it all back... Period.
<br />

<br />
No ones mentioned if you go to jail if you cant pay all the cash back in 5 years...
<br />

<br />
Only advice I can give to anyone is this... If your thinking of filing for  bankruptcy do it within the next 6 months before GWB signs the bill... You'll walk under the deadline and get to walking away from your debts.
<br />

<br />
If not dump every debt with the highest interest rate 1st and DO NOT create new debt or accept any debt "to get you by". Avoid any unsecured debt with any interest rate your not willing to accept. 
<br />

<br />
Hopefully theres people willing to learn enough from this to force the credit card companys to drop their interest rate to the point people can use them. If not its time to put those assholes out of business...
<br />

<br />
